---

Third-party components:

- pymupdf (PyMuPDF)
    License: AGPL-3.0-or-later
    https://github.com/pymupdf/PyMuPDF
    Used for: PDF text extraction. This is the reason Aerocrawl
    itself is AGPL-3.0 — pymupdf's license requires any distribution
    containing it to be AGPL-compatible.

- Playwright
    License: Apache-2.0
    https://github.com/microsoft/playwright
    Used for: headless browser scraping with stealth patches.

- FastAPI
    License: MIT
    https://github.com/tiangolo/fastapi

- uvicorn
    License: BSD-3-Clause
    https://github.com/encode/uvicorn

- Redis / redis-py
    License: BSD-3-Clause
    https://github.com/redis/redis-py

- arq
    License: MIT
    https://github.com/samuelcolvin/arq

- Caddy (installed separately on the VPS, not bundled)
    License: Apache-2.0
    https://caddyserver.com/

- pdfplumber
    License: MIT
    https://github.com/jsvine/pdfplumber

- Google Gemini API (used when GEMINI_API_KEY is set)
    License: Google API terms — https://ai.google.dev/terms
    NOT bundled; Aerocrawl calls the Google API on the user's behalf
    using their key.
